name: a woman by the river in a French ginguette
description: This photo was taken along the edges of Maine, a river in central France, in part of the Anjou vineyard. A ginguette, musicians who play guitar and accordion, something to eat, and above all something to drink: wine and beer. In this atmosphere nobody tries to show themselves, they are, and that's perfect. At the turn of a game of "pétanque", there was this woman who seemed to come out of a novel from the end of the 19th century. This shot is my favorite of this evening.
